Package io.github.jorgericovivas.rust_essentials.option

Record Class None<T>

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
io.github.jorgericovivas.rust_essentials.option.None<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the value.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Option<T>, Serializable
public record None<T>() extends Record implements Option<T>, Serializable
Represents an empty value, as it was a 'null' value;

Example: In searching an index of a List whose element matches a Predicate, the resulting value could be Option<Integer>, and when not present, the operation would return a None<Integer> containing no value, indicating the programmer the operation didn't find any value.

This is clearer than using a special value to indicate errors, like -1 would have been, but this way, the programmer doesn't need to remember these special values, and if you want to add information about why an operation couldn't be executed, you can use Err instead to follow the pattern of Result instead of that of Option.
